public class JournalTimeSeriesCollection
extends org.jfree.data.time.TimeSeriesCollection
implements JournalListener, javax.swing.event.ChangeListener

This class implements a time series collection for an fsfibu 2 Journal. The collection contains a bilancial time series for all entries admitted by a certain filter and optionally a moving average.

Author:
Simon Hampe

JournalTimeSeriesCollection

public JournalTimeSeriesCollection(Journal j,
                                   StackFilter f,
                                   boolean displayAverage,
                                   int averagePeriod)
Constructs a new TimeSeriesCollection.

Parameters:
j - The journal from which to take the data. If null, an empty dummy journal is created
f - The filter which determines the entries to take into account
displayAverage - Whether a moving average should be displayed additionally
averagePeriod - The time period in days for the moving average
